<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB00103</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT REGULATING THE PRODUCTION, IMPORTATION, SALE, PROVISION, USE, RECOVERY, COLLECTION, RECYCLING, AND DISPOSAL OF PLASTIC PRODUCTS</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : Seeks to regulate the production, use, recycling and disposal of plastic bags and other single-use plastics in the whole country. Provides for a gradual phase out of single-use plastics; a transition program for the shift to the use of biodegradable plastic bags; a Special Environment Fund for plastics regulation;  the role of local government units; a program for affected workers of the plastic industry; and support for affected manufacturers of plastic products for effective implementation of this Act.</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ALIAS NAME : “Plastic Products Regulation Act”</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>FORTUN, LAWRENCE &quot;LAW&quot; H.</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2019-07-01</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>CO-AUTHORS (Journal Entries) :</td></tr><tr><td>1. Pacquiao (R.) (000 2019-09-17)</td><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE ON RULES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REFERRAL TO THE COMMITTEE ON ECOLOGY ON 2019-07-23</td></tr></table>